<title>SOUTH AFRICA: TABLE - T&amp;N half yr shr dips, div cut.</title>
<headline>TABLE - T&amp;N half yr shr dips, div cut.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-08-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year to June 30</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - headline		37.5	  vs   50.4</p>
<p>    - attrib		  37.5	  vs   50.4</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 13.0	  vs   17.0</p>
<p>    Attrib income	    9.3	  vs   12.1</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   11.6	  vs   16.9</p>
<p>    Tax			  2.3	  vs    4.8</p>
<p>    Financing charges     12.1	  vs   12.3</p>
<p>    Turnover		 405.9	  vs  400.3</p>
<p>Full name: T&amp;N Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>* The company said it would issue capitalisation shares to shareholders registered on 19, the terms of which would be announced on September 15.</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said that no improvement was expected in original equipment demand which would continue to be weak in the light of increasing imported units and components. However, with the anticipated improved performance of its Friction Products Division, increased supply level on new export contracts and an interest rate reduction, an improvement in earnings was expected in the second half.</p>
